    <!--
        Spring utilizes the idea of an IOC container...
            How the Container is created is dependent on the configurations in this file.
        What Spring Bean?
            - A spring bean is a class that you told spring to manage its dependencies for you
         types of injection:
            - setter injection (through getters and setters)
            - constructor injection (through the constructor)
         Scope of a bean
            - Singleton (default): tells spring to only make one instance of that bean
            - Prototype: creates an instance whenever someone asks
            - Request: new instance will be created for every http request
            - Session: new instance will be created for every session
            - GlobalSession: single instance of that bean will exist for the entire sessionFactory
    -->


